		<div id="comment_body_64667010"><p><div class="quote"><p>We ever came up with is the idea that if you do it online on a computer it's a new legal framework and perfectly a-okay.</p></div><p>Easily fixable. Congress passes a law saying the FTC can regulate it. The supreme court rarely says that the government can't regulate something. It often says the executive branch can't regulate stuff the legislative branch didn't give it the power to regulate.</p><p>As it stands now, Congresses main goal to make money for themselves, or funnels money to their friends. If a law doesn't make themselves or their friends richer, it isn't going to be passed.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64667010">

